The paper proposes a concept to enable better communication between dataset creators and users, and help the AI community move toward greater transparency and accountability. It focuses on datasets and their characteristics, motivations, and potential skews. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.AI, cs.LG, and cs.CV, which are related to artificial intelligence, machine learning, and computer vision. Additionally, the paper also touches on issues related to privacy and security (cs.CR) and information retrieval (cs.IR) in the case of human-centric datasets.
